.Dd 2026-07-06
.Dt dset_find 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dset_find ,
.Nm dset_join ,
.Nm dset_joined
.Nd disjoint-set lookup and union operations
.Sh LIBRARY
IRIS C Library
.Pq Vt ilib_c
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In dsetuf.h
.Ft int
.Fo dset_find
.Fa "disjoint_set_t *ds"
.Fa "int x"
.Fc
.Ft void
.Fo dset_join
.Fa "disjoint_set_t *ds"
.Fa "int a"
.Fa "int b"
.Fc
.Ft int
.Fo dset_joined
.Fa "const disjoint_set_t *ds"
.Fa "int a"
.Fa "int b"
.Fc
.Bl -tag -width -5n -offset -6n
.It Implementation Macro Requirements (see \fIdsetuf\fR(7)):
.El
.Bl -tag -width 0
.El
.Bl -tag -width 2n
.It \fBdset_find\fR():
DSUF_IMPLEMENTATION
.It \fBdset_join\fR(), \fBdset_joined\fR():
DSUF_IMPLEMENTATION
.El
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Together,
.Fn dset_find ,
.Fn dset_join ,
and
.Fn dset_joined
form the query and merge interface of a disjoint-set: locating an element's representative,
merging two elements' sets, and testing whether two elements already belong to the
same set.
.Bl -tag
.It Fn dset_find
Locates the representative
.Pq root
of the set containing element
.Fa x ,
identified by
.Fa parent[x] == x ,
performing path compression along the way: every node visited has its parent pointer
rewritten to point directly at the root, so subsequent calls on the same elements
are faster.
.It Fn dset_join
Merges the sets containing elements
.Fa a
and
.Fa b
into a single set. If
.Fa a
and
.Fa b
already belong to the same set, the call has no effect. Otherwise, the
smaller of the two sets
.Pq by element count
is attached under the root of the larger, using the
.Va size
array to decide which is smaller; this union-by-size strategy bounds
the height of the resulting tree logarithmically.
.It Fn dset_joined
Tests whether
.Fa a
and
.Fa b
belong to the same set. It is equivalent to comparing the results of
calling
.Fn dset_find
on each element, and is provided as a convenience so callers do not
need to invoke
.Fn dset_find
directly for this common check.
.El
.Sh RETURN VALUE
.Pp
The
.Fn dset_find
and
.Fn dset_joined
functions return an integer. The former returns the representative
.Pq root
of the set containing
.Fa x
while the latter returns a value that can be used as a boolean.
.Pp
The
.Fn dset_join
function returns no value.
