.El
.D1 St -isoC-99
.Sh NOTES
The
.Fn dset_find ,
.Fn dset_join ,
and
.Fn dset_joined
functions perform no bounds checking.
Passing an index outside the half-open interval [0, \fIsize\fR) results in undefined behavior.
.Pp
The
.Fn dset_find
function is implemented recursively.
The maximum recursion depth is proportional to the height of the tree representing the set.
In practice, path compression rapidly reduces tree height, making deep recursion uncommon after the initial lookup operations.
.Pp
Although
.Fn dset_joined
accepts a
.Vt "const disjoint_set_t *"
argument, it internally casts away
.Dv const
to invoke
.Fn dset_find ,
which performs path compression by updating the internal parent array.
Consequently, the data structure may be modified even when accessed through a
.Dv const
pointer.
